      <p>Below are things that inspired me and I care about. I hope this can help you understand me better. My passions include: <a href="influences/#entrepreneurship">Entrepreneurship</a>, <a href="influences/#technology">Technology</a>, <a href="influences/#ucd">User-Centered Design</a>, <a href="influences/#sf">Science Fiction</a>, <a href="influences/#outdoors">Outdoors</a>.</p>

      <h2 id="entrepreneurship">Entrepreneurship</h2>
      <p>I want to create my own startup, it's just a matter of time! My first introduction to entrepreneurship was Guy Kawasaki and his book The Art of the Start. But when I moved to San Francisco, everything changed, I was part of a real startup. I learned a lot from the inside. Since the, I read a lot of articles. Pau Graham influenced me a lot. I loved Sam Altman's How to Start a Startup course at Stanford.</p>

